Hi — this demo showcases ChatMessagesComponent, ChatInputComponent, and ChatTypingIndicatorComponent working together as individual primitives rather than the composed ChatComponent.

Quick fact: Angular signals are lightweight reactive primitives that hold state and notify dependents (computed values and effects) when the value changes. They enable fine-grained reactivity, reducing reliance on Zone.js and making update propagation more predictable and efficient.

Example usage:
const count = signal(0);
const double = computed(() => count() * 2);
effect(() => console.log(double()));
